      "title": "I think Anthropic and OpenAI have found product-market fit",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/27/product-market-fit/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48296794",
      "score": 365,
      "comments": 455,
      "author": "simonw",
      "published": "2026-05-27T16:39:13Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Claude 3.5 Sonnet and GPT-4o drive massive API growth through integration in developer tools like Cursor and GitHub Copilot.",
        "Enterprises transition from simple chat interfaces to production-grade agentic workflows and custom RAG pipelines using native LLM tool-calling APIs.",
        "Rapidly declining token costs and expanding context windows make processing entire codebases economically viable for production AI engineering."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "What are some of your favourite developer tools?",
      "url": "https://lobste.rs/s/2jdvxa",
