      "score": 74,
      "comments": 105,
      "author": "dhruvp",
      "published": "2026-05-27T05:40:47Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Engineers highly favor Rust-based CLI upgrades like `ripgrep` (rg) and `fd` alongside `fzf` for ultra-fast terminal search and navigation.",
        "Tools like `direnv` for directory-specific environment variables and `asdf` or `mise` for multi-language runtime version management are widely recommended.",
        "Terminal multiplexers like `tmux` and interactive Git TUI tools like `lazygit` significantly optimize developer workflow efficiency over GUI alternatives."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Atom Exhaustion Is Not a Footgun. It's One Third of Our CVEs",
      "url": "https://erlef.org/blog/security/atom-exhaustion",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/lfusbg",
      "score": 15,
      "comments": 8,
      "author": "pushcx",
      "published": "2026-05-27T16:48:05Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Erlang and Elixir (BEAM) systems risk Denial of Service (DoS) VM crashes because dynamically created atoms are never garbage-collected.",
        "Untrusted input parsing driving dynamic atom creation accounts for approximately 33% of CVEs in the BEAM ecosystem.",
        "Mitigate this vulnerability by banning String.to_atom/1 and binary_to_atom/2, mandating safer existing_atom alternatives."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
